section.section:
If a plan submitted under this section meets the standards of this subtitle, the Secretary may waive the permit requirements of the subtitle and permit the submitting local or county health department to conduct cholesterol testing under this subtitle for a period of 12 months, provided that:
The submission adequately describes the cholesterol testing plan for the effective 12 months;
The local or county health department provides all information that the Secretary may reasonably require to determine compliance with this section;
The local or county health department agrees to make records available and submit reports to the Secretary as the Secretary may require;
Changes and amendments to the plan are submitted 60 days prior to proposed implementation; and
All changes and amendments to the plan are approved by the Secretary.
